		<p> {{ page.overview.intro|raw }}
            On the display in the front seat we showed ourselves where exactly we were currently.
            Steffi typed me at some point and showed me that we were directly over Plauen. Local time 4:45.
            Somewhere down there I have family that is now in the deepest dreams and has no idea that we are just so close and yet so far.
            When I fly by I sent my Omi an air kiss and then we were already in London.
            The flight was really bad, as far as the unfriendly staff and organization were concerned.
            They went out of food, both at dinner and breakfast. </p>
		<p> We had time to browse around at London Airport and have a little bit of breakfast before we made ourselves comfortable in Hamburg in a rather empty plane.
            It was so much space that each of us had their own row for themselves.
            I missed half of the flight and Steffi took photos of the islands that line up like a pearl line in front of the North Sea coast.
            From up here they look almost the same as the coral islands of the Great Barrier Reefs.
            I had the hope that I had slept longer and we had flown back to Australia.
            But when the typical German field economy and the many towns were seen, it became clear to me that we are almost at home again. </p>
